 to increase their faction in Surefall Glade.<br><br>We divide the guild up into level-based tiers, for an all-against-Chase battle, and the person who actually lands the killing blow gets a stack of a stat beverage of their choice. All participants get at least one stat beverage of my choice, and anyone I manage to kill (/snicker, yeah right) gets five stat beverages of my choice. Seeing as how most of my guild is moving into the 50's, I'm really dreading the 50+ tier of this event (I'm only 40); I suspect my life expectancy after the word &quot;Go!&quot; to be measured in nano-seconds.<br><br>Anyway, we should have some sort of a commemoration of the birthdate of our server in an RP spirit. Or perhaps we should all head to North Qeynos and zerg The Moss Snake. There are many of us, I'm sure, who remember being essentially unable to find a mob to kill for the first few hours the server was open (I think I saw more Gnoll Hunter's in QH those first few days than I have ever seen before or since combined).<br><br>/ramble off<br><br>Cheers, <p><p align="center"><b>Chase<br></b>Half-Elven <a href=http://interealms.com/ranger/>Ranger</a> of Tunare<br>40 seasons wandering the wood in defense of Her creatures<br>Guild Master Brewer of the<br><a href=http://hoc.eq.tripod.com>House of Carnage</a><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><BR><BR><select name=Things I can do with the stuff you throw away><option>Things I can do with the stuff you throw away<option>Brewing 250<option>Fletching 200<option>Pottery 183<option>Baking 182<option>Fishing 149<option>Smithing 115<option>Tailoring 109</select></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaxvs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maxvs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 3:50:25 pm)</font><br> 