 no interest in roleplay might get so tired of it that they will leave.  <br><br>I'm guessing that the majority of the good RP'ers are mid to high level, unless they recently started a new character.  With that in mind, please spend some of your time in the newbie/lowbie zones with the events that Syll has suggested.  Force the low level people to be subjected to it.  The ones that complain, well.../ignore.  The ones that play along, you just made them a part of your community.<br><br>I know it is difficult for a group that has been together for some time, and feels like they are under seige by a bunch of newcomers, to actually accept the newcomers that desire to fit in.  Knowing how many of the FV veterans feel, I am a bit reluctant to start any interaction with a higher level player.  And only two characters with a last name have started a conversation with me.  I'm sure there are others like me, completely new to all of this, that feel the same intimidation.  So, I ask the old-timers to spend time roleplaying around the low levels, and with the low levels.  It is ultimately up to you to make the newcomers with good intentions feel welcome.  Lead by example.  Show us how to be good roleplayers, dammit! *smiles*<br><br>I'll shut my newbie mouth now.  If someone has said all this before, my apologies for beating a dead horse.  And thank you for taking the time to read what I had to say.<br><br>Mangudai,<br>Shadowknight of the 10th skull<br>Servant of Bertoxxulous<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/immortalkindred/images/colors.gif